  {
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "So I tried that @bobylito but then when you build custom react widgets and want to publish them as jsdelivr `<script>` (because you do not want to limit your widgets to a public that is only browserify/webpack) that's an issue.\n\nFor us, we can rely on some \"DI\" by reusing the instantsearch.deps.\\* in widgets but then if your custom widget wants to reuse any existing react component (say react-google-maps) then it will fail because we are not be able to inject \"OUR\" react into their component.\n\nThe underlying reused component (google-maps) will just try to require(\"react\") which will fail.\n",
    "created_at": "2015-11-03T08:08:35Z",
    "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/373#issuecomment-153284185",
